{
  "name": "SpatialNav-MP3D",
  "description": "SpatialNav (arXiv 2601.06806, Zhang et al. 2026) reasoning graph for discrete R2R / REVERIE navigation on Matterport3D. Forked from NavGPT-MP3D with three SpatialNav-specific additions: (1) Spatial Scene Graph (SSG) — agent-centric top-down map + instruction-aligned nearby-object retrieval from MP3D ground-truth .house + _semantic.ply; (2) 'Final Answer > Action' parse priority (reversed from NavGPT's raise-on-both); (3) max_scratchpad_length=4096 and 'Current Top-down Map: [SSG map image]' observation label. The SSG map IMAGE flows through a persisted `scene_graph` port: init_render_map seeds it on step 0, step_render_map refreshes it after each successful navigation, iter_out carries it forward, and the orchestrator LLM receives it via a dedicated scene_graph IMAGE port on the prompt. SSG data layer (SceneGraphMapper + SceneObjectGraph + SentenceTransformer) is lazy-loaded on first render/query and held process-wide. Requires: env_mp3d + navgpt_mp3d_tools (for BLIP-2 + R-CNN perception) + ssg + spatialnav nodesets.",
